  "market_context": "USDCAD on the 1-hour formed a bearish candle two closure, setting up a continuation lower. Analyst marks the equilibrium (EQ) and previous day low as references, identifying two fair value gaps below EQ as potential points of interest for a short continuation.",
  "key_observation": "Price did not respect the upper fair value gap, and no candle two closure formed at the POI; instead a candle three closure printed, engulfing prior candles and establishing a new protected swing high to anticipate continuation lower.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified a bearish candle two closure on USDCAD 1H signaling continuation potential.",
    "Marked out the EQ level and the previous day low as the key reference levels, noting price can form its high below EQ without touching it.",
    "Highlighted two fair value gaps below EQ as candidate points of interest rather than guessing which one reacts.",
    "Waited for a swing/protected swing to form; observed the first fair value gap was not respected and removed it.",
    "Checked for a candle two closure at the POI — none formed — then identified a candle three closure as the reversal trigger, creating a new protected swing.",
    "Anticipated the higher time frame wick was complete and projected price to trade down through the previous day low as first target.",
    "Confirmed the reversal with the indicator showing SMT divergence with DXY, a change in state of delivery, and the T-spot (EQ) marked as the POI."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded lower and traded through the previous day low as the first target, confirming the bearish continuation.",
  "lessons": "When a candle two closure does not print at a point of interest, a candle three closure (engulfing closure) can still form a valid protected swing. Combined with SMT, CISD, and a defined POI like EQ, it provides a high-probability continuation entry.",
